        <h2>How does it work?</h2>

        <p class="lead">
            The idea behind VersionEye is that it monitors your package managers project files on GitHub / Bitbucket / Stash.
            Project files like Gemfile, package.json, composer.json, pom.xml, Podfile and many others.
            That way VersionEye knows which open source dependencies you are using and based on that
            it can send you notifications to <b>security vulnerabilities</b>, <b>license violations</b> and <b>outdated versions</b>
            which matters to you.
        </p>

        <p class="lead">
            Currently these package managers are supported:
        </p>

        <ul style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 1.3em;">
            <li><a href="https://getcomposer.org/">Composer</a> (PHP)</li>
            <li><a href="https://bundler.io/">Bundler</a> (Ruby)</li>
            <li><a href="https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pip/">PIP</a> (Python)</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.npmjs.org/">NPM</a> (Node.JS)</li>
            <li><a href="https://yarnpkg.com/en/">Yarn</a> (Node.JS)</li>
            <li><a href="http://bower.io/">Bower</a> (JavaScript)</li>
            <li><a href="http://cocoapods.org/">CocoaPods</a> (Objective-C)</li>
            <li><a href="http://maven.apache.org/">Maven</a> (Java)</li>
            <li><a href="http://www.scala-sbt.org/">SBT</a> (Scala)</li>
            <li><a href="https://gradle.org">Gradle</a> (Groovy)</li>
            <li><a href="http://leiningen.org/">Leiningen</a> (Clojure)</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.nuget.org/">Nuget</a> (Microsoft .NET platform)</li>
